.TH DHWEBCHATD 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
dhwebchatd \- run aprsd's webchat command for DigiHub's APRS WebChat
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dhwebchatd
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dhwebchatd
runs
.BR aprsd (1)'s
.B webchat
command (provided by the
.B aprsd\-webchat\-extension
package), giving a browser\-based interface for sending and receiving
APRS text messages.
.PP
.B dhwebchatd
is designed to run under systemd as the
.B dhwebchat.service
unit, not to be started manually. Unlike
.BR dhgpsmonitor.service
or
.BR dhweb.service ,
it is
.B not
enabled automatically by
.BR install.sh ;
it stays off until
.BR dhwebchat (1)
turns it on.
.PP
Unlike
.BR dhnoded (1),
.B dhwebchatd
does
.B not
need exclusive access to any radio hardware: it connects to Dire
Wolf's KISS\-over\-TCP interface
.RI ( localhost:8001 ,
Dire Wolf's default), which every Direwolf\-backed mode
.RI ( tnc ,
.IR tnc300b ,
.IR tracker ,
.IR digipeater ,
.IR node )
already exposes. This is why APRS WebChat is an independent toggle
like
.BR dhrig (1)/dhpat (1)/dhardop (1),
rather than one of
.BR dhmode (1)'s
mutually\-exclusive modes \-\- it can run alongside whichever of those
is already active. If none of them is active, WebChat still starts
(and its browser UI still works for composing/reading), but nothing
moves over RF until a Direwolf\-backed mode is selected with
.BR dhmode (1).
.PP
The configuration file itself is generated by
.B webchatconf.py
(invoked internally by
.BR dhwebchat (1),
not run directly), which reads
.I $HOME/.dhinfo 's
.IR callsign ,
.IR lat ,
and
.I lon
fields and writes
.IR $HOME/.config/aprsd/aprsd.conf .
It configures aprsd for RF\-only operation
.RI ( aprs_network
disabled) \-\- no APRS\-IS/internet connection is needed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Turn WebChat on (starts/enables this service automatically):
.B dhwebchat on
.TP
Check the running service's status and recent log output:
.B systemctl status dhwebchat
.br
.B journalctl \-u dhwebchat \-f
.TP
Open WebChat's own browser UI once running:
.B http://<digihub\-host>:8888
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $HOME/.config/aprsd/aprsd.conf
Generated configuration; regenerated every time
.BR dhwebchat (1)
is turned on. Do not edit by hand \-\- changes are overwritten on the
next
.RI "" "dhwebchat on" .
.TP
.I /etc/digihub/webchat.env
Supplies
.BR DigiHubvenv ,
written by
.BR install.sh .
.TP
.I /etc/systemd/system/dhwebchat.service
The systemd unit that runs this daemon, installed and enabled by
.BR dhwebchat (1)
on first use.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.B dhwebchatd
does not exit under normal operation; it runs until stopped (e.g. by
systemd).
.TP
.B 1
The shared UI library could not be loaded,
.B aprsd
is not installed in the DigiHub Python virtual environment, or
.BR dhwebchat (1)
has not been turned on yet (no
.IR aprsd.conf ).
